cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.HC 

This paper is about planning for service robots to tidy up home environments, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper proposes a novel planning method that involves learning the distributions of co-occurrence probability of objects and places to tidy up, which suggests the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method also uses multimodal sensor information, which could involve computer vision (cs.CV). The learning of the probabilistic generative model could also involve machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper focuses on the interaction between the robot and the environment, which could involve human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
